The paper presents a new adaptive predictive controller for constrained linear systems, which involves the use of receding horizon optimization and tube MPC controller. The paper focuses on the control and estimation aspects of the system, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the Control Systems (cs.SY) sub-category. Additionally, the use of optimization and machine learning techniques such as MPC and parameter estimation suggests that it could also belong to the Machine Learning (cs.LG), Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI), and Statistical Learning (cs.SI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper also mentions the use of robust exponential stability and convergence of estimates, which suggests that it could belong to the Neural and Evolutionary Computing (cs.NE) sub-category.
